From 35025183199a24f4d445c0f16644e10d197212a1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: v0 <it+v0agent@vercel.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 05:28:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(kit/api-docs): promote FieldGroup + FieldItem +
 useFieldAnchor
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add three data-agnostic slices to the api-docs kit so future doc-style
projects reuse them instead of re-designing:

- ApiDocsFieldGroup: labelled field-group container (h2 + optional count).
- ApiDocsFieldItem: recursive field row (requiredness tri-state, default,
  condition, enum, constraint notes, lifecycle) + collapsible subfields.
  The field data model travels inline with the component (FieldNode,
  EnumValue, EnumVariant, FieldNote, …) per the kit slice-self-containment
  convention; EnumTable is left untouched.
- useFieldAnchor: deep-linking composable, self-contained (replaceState +
  self-managed scroll, no Vue Router scrollBehavior dependency). Consumers
  call initFromHash() on mount; an optional router.options hash tweak only
  removes a cold-load scroll flash and is NOT shipped by the kit.

FieldContractNote is renamed to the more neutral FieldNote on the kit side.
registry.json gains field-group + field-item entries; gallery gets a field
tree demo; references reclassify these as kit slices and drop the orphaned
ContractNote row.

Co-authored-by: v0 <it+v0agent@vercel.com>
